subject: You‚Äôre invited to GTC Paris‚Äîexplore the impact of agentic AI across industries
snippet: Hi Anand, I'm thrilled to invite you to NVIDIA GTC Paris, taking place at VivaTech 2025 on June 10‚Äì12. Join me and thousands of industry leaders to explore how AI agents are helping solve our
content:
Hi  Anand,
I‚Äôm thrilled to invite you to NVIDIA GTC Paris <https://go.nvidianews.com/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGa2PIkxZBG3OY2_b1H-zY_1NGxS7m4d5G7Jr4pEeMOUqkQa3jfGoSdS2Jd3UlIwLQndtEMLOM=>, taking place at VivaTech 2025 on June 10‚Äì12. Join me and thousands of industry leaders to explore how AI agents are helping solve our largest, most complex challenges.

Don‚Äôt miss the chance to hear directly from NVIDIA CEO Jensen Huang in his must-see keynote <https://go.nvidianews.com/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGa2PIkxUZzGGSXQ2FVu_a9lY5-LJ2b01NTyDqsDDw4qHJXIPGlJAxlg0gg2S9nns2arpKTHEY=> at VivaTech Paris, and explore the latest in AI and advanced technologies with hands-on workshops, certifications, demos, and expert-led sessions <https://go.nvidianews.com/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGa2PIkxVgcM394F6hUKSgOR7Lt-nm3ZdElP_t_NTMKgQukY-nKQxfsBzAlKTc4yqj4lhCB4BA=>, featuring industry leaders such as Vincent Van Steenbergen, CEO and Founder, ThinkDeepAI; Asmita Dubey, Chief Digital and Marketing Officer, L‚ÄôOr√©al; Aude Gandon, Global CMO, Nestl√©; and Philipp Lorenz, CTO, Basecamp Research. 

Browse through our hand-picked lineup of agentic AI sessions <https://go.nvidianews.com/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGa2PIkxctkU6gyhxTRt6SWjhpKzyR_PgPzMDScpb6EGikunrkVSsLWSscOgCF-FrgUzXnHIJQ=>, and check out more of my personal top picks:



	- Shaping the AI Future: From Sovereign AI to Scalable AI Factories [GP1126 <https://go.nvidianews.com/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGa2PIkxV_A7PbRofe0wPHSnXxqrTs4AUPgjIwt3_daVA9MZr4vZz7pwypLk7b3FNqVB5gBsGU=>]
	- Building and Customizing AI Models for European Applications [GP1046 <https://go.nvidianews.com/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGa2PIkxUxheAyVD20Aid9lTkxXoUBDdfCW8AFKfsFf2YKY4YT9WzAT7wcFcuhNPCKKfGeFBTQ=>]
	- AI-Powered Personalized Marketing and Advertisement [GP1076 <https://go.nvidianews.com/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGa2PIkxeKJ2sjoPWWgvahcAh_K3Q4DOJHT3fAVyLi84426IEUlSXtGBXQxKENb9jDtaEW0Sk4=>]
	- Breaking the Drug Discovery Data Bottleneck With AI [GP1014 <https://go.nvidianews.com/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGa2PIkxUh8dS7stL6Gc9hNqaKJdYt5EzspjykRkVJ7mGRhj94WBfiMKQWE1QXCB4XsvGfoL5M=>]
	- Leveraging Foundation Models for Next-Generation Autonomous Vehicles and Cabin AI [GP1041 <https://go.nvidianews.com/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGa2PIkxcCCVEDepW79WgVn-9KOg_iuiRC21seV3Muveh3E0yVJ6XfmcimBagyyZg1MKlYtN7w=>]
	- How to Build an Agentic AI System Using the Best Tools and Frameworks [GP1075 <https://go.nvidianews.com/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGa2PIkxeoZaRh0Gj6_KXaCl_5Vid7DM35Cs12yVYKKjZz6DErfpcU9WGBrzgCsZb2QV-qLW5k=>]


Register now <https://go.nvidianews.com/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGa2PIkxZBG3OY2_b1H-zY_1NGxS7m4d5G7Jr4pEeMOUqkQa3jfGoSdS2Jd3UlIwLQndtEMLOM=> to reserve your spot. GTC Paris is more than just a conference. It‚Äôs an opportunity to connect, learn, and share with the brightest minds in AI and beyond. I‚Äôm looking forward to seeing you there.
Best Regards,

Kari Briski
VP, Generative AI Software for Enterprise, NVIDIA

subject: Coming February 3, 2026:¬† A new era for Cisco certifications
snippet: Read about exciting changes to Learn with Cisco's industry-leading certification portfolio. View online Hi Cisco Networking Academy Partners, Instructors, and Students, On February 3, 2026, Learn
content:
Hi Cisco Networking Academy Partners, Instructors, and Students,




On February 3, 2026, Learn with Cisco will introduce exciting changes to its industry-leading certification portfolio, shaping the next generation of networking careers in the age of AI, network automation, and cybersecurity. With this update, most of our certifications will more clearly follow three certification levels for advancing from entry to expert using the framework learners know and trust:


	- CCNA (Associate)
	- CCNP (Professional)
	- CCIE (Expert)
What‚Äôs changing includes:
DevNet Certifications Are Transitioning to Cisco Automation Certifications
What this means for you: The DevNet Associate certification exam will be renamed to CCNA Automation. No changes will be made to the exam topics for this certification. Anyone holding an active DevNet Associate certification will automatically be transitioned to CCNA Automation after February 3, 2025. We are not renaming the DevNet Associate course from Cisco Networking Academy at this time.
Cybersecurity certifications will be CCNA Cybersecurity and CCNP Cybersecurity
What this means for you: The Cybersecurity Associate certification will be renamed to CCNA Cybersecurity. No changes will be made to the exam topics for this certification. Anyone holding an active Cybersecurity Associate exam will automatically be transitioned to CCNA Cybersecurity after February 3, 2025. We are not renaming the CyberOps Associate course from Cisco Networking Academy at this time.
Additionally, please note: 



	- The CCNA certification exam and name are not changing.
	- The CCNP Enterprise certification exams and names are not changing.






We are working on Frequently Asked Questions for Cisco Networking Academy and will follow up with more details in the coming weeks.




See the full announcement from Cisco Certifications here: Coming February 3, 2026: A new era for Cisco certifications <http://nsmail.netacad.com/MDU5LVZGWi04MzQAAAGatxKcHNQs67J44vtP-GQ9hnryCXItWgiZ4WfowFyGMiWujEQ24AZixZmJY8sndpGU0NBdXP0=>.

The future of networking is intelligent. Be ready.

subject: The Future of Tech Needs You! Cisco Learn-a-Thon
snippet: View online Cisco Networking Academy Logo The Future of Tech Needs You! Join the International Girls in ICT Day Learn-A-Thon! Technology is shaping every industry, creating millions of new job
content:
The Future of Tech Needs You!
Join the International Girls in ICT Day Learn-A-Thon!
Technology is shaping every industry, creating millions of new job opportunities‚Äîbut women are still vastly underrepresented in tech. With only 29.2% of the STEM workforce being female, we cannot afford to leave women behind. Diversity fuels innovation, and closing the gender gap is the only way forward. 

That‚Äôs why Cisco Networking Academy is launching the International Girls in ICT Day Learn-A-Thon‚Äîan opportunity to gain essential tech skills, explore future careers, and take your first step into the world of technology. No matter your background, tech has a place for you! 

Choose from three exciting courses and start learning today: 

Introduction to Cybersecurity ‚Äì Discover how to protect digital landscapes in today‚Äôs connected world. Enroll now <http://nsmail.netacad.com/MDU5LVZGWi04MzQAAAGaG4FOLH4hU9umkrLGdy0HnLP4MI2710lURvaVavwny9qVjG-piiS2wOifRlAd3TmAGUXMsOA=>

Introduction to Data Science ‚Äì Learn how to uncover insights from data and make informed decisions. Enroll now <http://nsmail.netacad.com/MDU5LVZGWi04MzQAAAGaG4FOLMk36eNBSCzLq4Z16t0Rrd8KDBBKlCHa5eoy7kQVLwEUxmbwdcR46tEqhrjF84OKq18=>

Introduction to Modern AI ‚Äì Explore the power of artificial intelligence and its role in shaping the future. Enroll now <http://nsmail.netacad.com/MDU5LVZGWi04MzQAAAGaG4FOLF13Up_ZkoL2sedBRd_nsUPGM1g8Uf_Oj4X1IZZUJJsnxycsPoI2T6XLQdBxR-OIqO4=>

Don‚Äôt miss this chance to gain valuable skills and be part of the next generation of female tech leaders!The future of tech needs your voice, talent, and ideas. Let‚Äôs break barriers together!
The future is here. Don‚Äôt miss this chance to discover how you can kick-start your career in the exciting world of technology!

subject: NetAcad Student Newsletter ‚Äì April 2025
snippet: View online Hello NetAcad Student, Welcome to your latest quarterly newsletter, packed with important updates, exciting new learning options, great events, and more. Read on! Important Updates Action
content:
Hello Anand,
 

The new experience at NetAcad.com is live! We're excited to see that many classes are already underway. This milestone marks a significant step in our mission to power an inclusive future for all. In our ongoing spirit of innovation, we will continue to add more teaching and learning features, courses, and resources.


To our partners and educators: thank you for your continued support, patience, and trust in Cisco Networking Academy. We highly value your collaboration and look forward to the positive impact we will continue to make together in our communities around the world.


Scroll down for tips on the new NetAcad.com platform, new courses, orientation learning collections, and more. We are also thrilled to unveil a whole new page dedicated to careers promoting current job opportunities with new employment partners like Indeed, the #1 job search platform (currently U.S. only).


And with Cybersecurity Awareness Month fast-approaching, you can get ready by checking out the first in our 10-part virtual series (see the Events section)! We also have a campaign 
Sourcebook forthcoming, so be on the lookout for this awesome guide that will help you and your instructors promote opportunities and attract even more students. Finally, don't forget to remind your instructors to encourage their students to check out the new Find yourself in the future and Women Rock-IT special events coming soon.
First report released
The AI-Enabled ICT Workforce Consortium - led by Cisco with 8 leading tech companies plus key advisors - releases first report. Looks at effects of AI on top 50 ICT jobs, with actionable training recommendations to enable an AI-powered workforce.
Update to legal agreements - August 26
Stay tuned for updates to The Cisco Networking Academy membership guide, Terms and Conditions, privacy documents, and Packet Tracer Distribution Terms on August 26.
End-of-life: Continuing Education (CE) credits
Cisco Networking Academy is exiting the Cisco Continuing Education (CE) Credits program. Learn more <http://nsmail.netacad.com/MDU5LVZGWi04MzQAAAGZ_UT0QBvG0A04gKY0Q3GJw84Y9yr_N-zTYFtK9dg8gWneSbhk5CM1ORfHbjO-1MOtuQ4yhIU=>
Journey to Convergence
Visit Convergence Hub
Keep track of everything to do with Convergence of SkillsForAll.com and NetAcad.com on the Convergence Hub.
FINAL CHECKLIST
Convergence this month!
Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet
1. Downtime: 72 hours
Both NetAcad.com and SkillsForAll.com will be down for 72 hours. Start and end times depend on your location.

Take note <http://nsmail.netacad.com/MDU5LVZGWi04MzQAAAGZ_UT0PwZtArAh3S0ZdaVYSJZSavQP28BF3Va4lNXq81g6TPekMr_yqYSvQVTqUyHMpqjj6-Q=>
2.¬†Maintain downtime access
to Cisco Packet Tracer during planned downtime, especially for the 72 hours both sites will be down for convergence.

Prepare <http://nsmail.netacad.com/MDU5LVZGWi04MzQAAAGZ_UT0PwwvcHF3mgIF_nF2bw1KX3BI2hGs4qH8srDvwexxugoiRot_cIjeHoUppcPe-ZiKKs0=>
Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet
3. Quick Start Guide

4. Understand simplified roles
See how the number of roles are simplifying in the¬†new NetAcad.com.¬†
View <http://nsmail.netacad.com/MDU5LVZGWi04MzQAAAGZ_UT0P9skU_OlQXKbVu8TkPDH6H4GeXX0uiGYMBybcpzc61LKHdgUXSabmxOpDn8FPipVJbI=>
Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet
5. Start course customizations now

IPD Course Customization recordings cover how to migrate course customizations to the new NetAcad.com.¬†And you don't need to wait for convergence! Start building content now then add to courses from August 26.¬†
Replay IPD <http://nsmail.netacad.com/MDU5LVZGWi04MzQAAAGZ_UT0P6RqLWQC4gYiccDOrGraZ7kI3FYCsqSSxSG5WAQjNw7Jq5yVkgHF2v-AKv2XF90VCsY=>
6.¬†Are you ready for the new¬†NetAcad.com?
Three August IPD sessions continue preparing educators for convergence:¬†
1) Top 5 Instructor Tasks
2) Academy Management
3) Are you Ready ‚Äì convergence overview.¬†
Register IPD <http://nsmail.netacad.com/MDU5LVZGWi04MzQAAAGZ_UT0P6RqLWQC4gYiccDOrGraZ7kI3FYCsqSSxSG5WAQjNw7Jq5yVkgHF2v-AKv2XF90VCsY=>
Course Updates
Course translations
Arabic and Ukrainian Networking course translations are now available as instructor-led.

End-of-life date has been set for Cisco Networking Academy CCNP Enterprise: Core Networking (ENCOR) and CCNP Enterprise: Advanced Routing and Services (ENARSI).

Julio Lezcano, Panama <http://nsmail.netacad.com/MDU5LVZGWi04MzQAAAGZ_UT0P7Qa6Kdgxcr2HBipjIWhEZDx09Lw75L-3DI22E10NKaXCMZse6Pj-Nq8nz41bWk2uvk=>¬† I¬† Dr Gabriella Arellano, United States <http://nsmail.netacad.com/MDU5LVZGWi04MzQAAAGZ_UT0P2cWKmP83V-UyVcgM1z25Wp0mRDQHrwTCuhlkWCtMiVQVCdI8-r2Y_BasZYChrA50hk=>¬† I¬† Tully, Australia <http://nsmail.netacad.com/MDU5LVZGWi04MzQAAAGZ_UT0QNYvaLjs1lBX2R3RSElerf5FOku_P8CH8XH_3cnlSXAKQfPPXs1W8fzVwNuvMxadsb8=>

	- Real-world case studies

subject: Certifications, AI Challenges & Exclusive Events in April
snippet: Join a Guinness World Record AI lesson, earn your GitHub Certification and meet GitHub COO Kyle Daigle. Student Newsletter March 2025 Hey anand-chaniyara-college, April brings fresh opportunities to
content:
Join a Guinness World Record AI lesson, earn your GitHub Certification and meet GitHub COO Kyle Daigle.

( https://github.com/education )

********************
*Student Newsletter*
********************

**********
March 2025
**********

Hey anand-chaniyara-college,
April brings fresh opportunities to level up your tech skills and connect with the global developer community.

*Coming up next:*

*1.* Earn your GitHub Foundations Certification in 5 weeks
*2.* Join the Microsoft AI Skills Fest
*3.* Participate in BioHackathon

*4.* Take part in MLH Global Hack Week
*5.* Attend Kyle Daigle‚Äôs Fireside Chats
*6.* Discover Copilot AI Agent Mode
*7.* Build your own tech tutorials

*****************************************************************************
*Start your GitHub Foundations Certification today with our Exam Prep Course*
*****************************************************************************

Don't let your free voucher ( https://education.github.com/experiences/foundations_certificate ) go to waste, join our *five week prep course starting today* , March 31st, in the GitHub Community to get resources, practice exam questions, expert help, and more so you can pass the GitHub Foundations Exam.

Get started today ( https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/154502 )

**************************************************
*Master AI skills at the Microsoft AI Skills Fest*
**************************************************

Let's make history together. Build & showcase your AI Skills while attempting to set a *GUINNESS WORLD RECORDS‚Ñ¢* title attempt for most users to take an online multi-level artificial intelligence lesson in 24 hours. Don‚Äôt miss the activities beginning on April 7 at 23:00 UTC.

Register now ( https://aiskillsfest.event.microsoft.com/ )

**********************************************
*Solve biology challenges at the BioHackathon*
**********************************************

On April 11th, GitHub is sponsoring an *in-person Hackthon in Sao Paulo* , Brazil, for students.
Learn how to leverage AI while saving the planet, win swag as prizes and meet other environmentally conscious coders. Hosted by GitHub, with nonprofit ProgramEarth.

Sign up here ( https://lu.ma/0zq3i4f4 )

*****************************************************
*M* *L* *H* *Global Hack Week: API - April 11th-17th*
*****************************************************

Join the Major League Hacking Community at Global Hack Week: *API week, coming up April 11-17th*. At this free event, you'll have the opportunity to earn swag, attend workshops, and network with the community of builders while you build, explore, and learn all about APIs!

Register now ( https://ghw.mlh.io/events/api-week )

*************************************************************
*Chat with Kyle Daigle at the exclusive Fireside Chat events*
*************************************************************

Join GitHub COO Kyle Daigle in India for an exclusive Fireside Chat & AMA! You're invited to discover the future of software development, ¬†career pathways, and India‚Äôs growing developer community. Mark your calendars for *April 4th in Bengaluru and April 8th in Mumbai* !

Sign up now ( gh.io/kdindia25 )

*****************************************************
*Discover Copilot AI Agent Mode in our new blog post*
*****************************************************

Our latest blog post dives into AI agent mode's strengths, comparing it with Copilot Edits to help you choose the right tool for tasks like debugging complex code or streamlining multi-file projects. GitHub Education students *get free access to Copilot Pro* via the Student Developer Pack ( https://education.github.com/pack ) , making it easy to put these tips into practice.

Find out more ( https://gh.io/AAvar9z )

********************************************************
*Build your own tech from scratch with guided tutorials*
********************************************************

The 'build-your-own-x' repo offers a hands-on way to recreate simplified versions of your favourite technologies from scratch, gaining a deeper understanding of programming concepts along the way.

Build your own tech ( https://github.com/codecrafters-io/build-your-own-x )

( https://www.instagram.com/githubeducation/?hl=en ) ( https://www.facebook.com/GitHubEducation/ ) ( https://www.threads.net/@githubeducation ) ( https://twitter.com/githubeducation ) ( https://bsky.app/profile/githubeducation.bsky.social ) ( https://www.linkedin.com/showcase/github-education/ ) ( https://www.youtube.com/@githubeducation4427 ) ( https://www.twitch.tv/githubeducation )

Build production-ready generative AI solutions to transform your organization
In recent years, AI Inference‚Äì‚Äìthe process of running trained models to generate predictions‚Äîhas become a major focus in AI development, especially with the rise of large language models (LLMs) like GPT, Llama, and Gemini. For the successful use of AI inference, organizations need a full-stack approach that supports the end-to-end AI life cycle and tools that enable teams to meet their goals. With NVIDIA AI Enterprise stack we enable enterprises to build production-ready generative AI solutions to transform your organization. 

 Join us for an engaging webinar where we'll explore key considerations for deploying and scaling generative AI in production, including the critical role of AI inference. 

 Don't miss out on this opportunity to accelerate your enterprise journey with NVIDIA AI Enterprise software:

 In this webinar, you'll gain a deep understanding of LLM inference theory and applications, learning about:


	- Efficient prompt processing and token-generation techniques
	- Inference performance optimisations using TRT-LLM and NVIDIA Triton
	- LLM performance measurement with GenAI-Perf, hosted on TensorRT-LLM and Triton, and a text summarisation use case
	- Real-world case studies


Don't miss this opportunity to enhance your expertise or master a new technology. Plus, receive a FREE NVIDIA self-paced training course <https://go.nvidianews.com/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGZCO3COY_fFWHmXpi8nNtb-SZbgxQUDD-0PS-IDISHWHLZqxFgyhZHRylCCwJOidaaUTCbVpk=>¬†(valued at up to USD 90) when you attend this webinar.

This year‚Äôs conference will be our most ambitious yet, featuring 1,000+ sessions, expanded venues, hands-on technical workshops, and the opportunity to connect with the brightest minds shaping the future of AI and accelerated computing.

subject: Level üÜô with free certifications, hackathons & more
snippet: Explore free exam vouchers, open research grants, AI hackathons, and a flexible practice platform in this month's newsletter. Student Newsletter February 2025 Hey anand-chaniyara-college, This
content:
Explore free exam vouchers, open research grants, AI hackathons, and a flexible practice platform in this month‚Äôs newsletter.

( https://github.com/education )

********************
*Student Newsletter*
********************

*************
February 2025
*************

Hey anand-chaniyara-college,
This month‚Äôs newsletter has a bit of everything: new ways to showcase your skills, open research funding, hackathons to ignite your coding passion, and a platform to sharpen your practice. Whether you‚Äôre diving into AI-assisted development, looking to participate in an inclusive research project, or aiming to boost your r√©sum√©, we‚Äôve got you covered.

***********************************************************
*Hackathon Heroes: Fueling Innovation with MLH & Hack Club*
***********************************************************

( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1hzhdjXb5_E&ab_channel=MajorLeagueHacking )

At GitHub Education, we‚Äôre proud to power hackathons with Major League Hacking (MLH) ( https://mlh.io/ ) ‚Äî1 million members strong, reaching *1 in 3* *U.S.* *CS grads* ‚Äîand Hack Club ( https://hackclub.com/ ) , whose High Seas event drew *20,000+ signups* and over *7k new projects*.

These gatherings spark incredible creativity, from running Doom in a PDF ( https://github.com/Rochet2/DOOM-in-PDF ) to building a Minecraft server in Rust, and help students level up on GitHub. In fact, *most MLH members* become more active on GitHub after joining, thanks in part to the Student Developer Pack ( https://education.github.com/pack ) and GitHub Copilot.

( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5iaO0r09yRA&ab_channel=MajorLeagueHacking )

Curious to see hackathons in action? Check out ‚èØÔ∏è MLH‚Äôs GitHub-powered highlights ( https://youtu.be/1hzhdjXb5_E ) or their ‚èØÔ∏è 24-hour ‚ÄúSquid Game‚Äù robot build ( https://youtu.be/5iaO0r09yRA ) ‚Äîthen sign up ( https://mlh.io/ ) to bring your next big idea to life!

******************************************************
Build Your GitHub Skills with Certifications & Copilot
******************************************************

( https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/150827 )

Looking to boost your coding skills and job prospects? If you‚Äôre a *verified student* , you can take the *GitHub Foundations Certification exam* at no cost through the Student Developer Pack ( https://education.github.com/pack ). It covers essential GitHub topics like version control and collaboration‚Äîcapabilities employers value in real-world development. Need a place to start? The Microsoft Learning Path for GitHub Foundations ( https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/paths/github-foundations/ ) offers a step-by-step guide. Once you‚Äôre ready, visit the Foundations Certificate page ( https://education.github.com/experiences/foundations_certificate ) to redeem your free voucher.

Want to go further? Verified students also get *GitHub Copilot Pro* , which has more features than the free tier and helps you code faster and smarter. Check out the Copilot Learning Path ( https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/paths/copilot/ ) on Microsoft Learn or explore the Essentials of GitHub Copilot ( https://resources.github.com/learn/pathways/copilot/essentials/essentials-of-github-copilot/ ) to see how AI can streamline your workflow. By pairing a recognized certification with advanced AI coding skills, you‚Äôll be on track to build great projects‚Äîand stand out when it‚Äôs time to apply for your next opportunity!

*****************************************************************
Code with AI Hackathon (Microsoft D&I and Code; Without Barriers)
*****************************************************************

https://msit.events.teams.microsoft.com/event/e9cc0f8e-d768-48f9-8e4a-2a8f90b78267@72f988bf-86f1-41af-91ab-2d7cd011db47 ( https://www.orcaopen.org/ )

*March 8, 2025* ‚Äîmark your calendars for the Code with AI Virtual Hackathon ( https://msit.events.teams.microsoft.com/event/e9cc0f8e-d768-48f9-8e4a-2a8f90b78267@72f988bf-86f1-41af-91ab-2d7cd011db47 ) , aimed at empowering *female university students* across the Asia-Pacific region. Hosted by Microsoft D&I, this event combines a quick intro to GitHub and DevOps, an expert Q&A on careers in tech, a guided coding session featuring *GitHub Copilot* , and a *Fastest Coder Challenge*. Reserve your spot, hone your AI skills, and meet fellow female innovators.

Event details & registration ( https://msit.events.teams.microsoft.com/event/e9cc0f8e-d768-48f9-8e4a-2a8f90b78267@72f988bf-86f1-41af-91ab-2d7cd011db47 )

*****************************************
Free Learning Opportunities with Exercism
*****************************************

https://exercism.org/ ( https://exercism.org/ )

Whether you‚Äôre a beginner or a seasoned coder, Exercism ( https://exercism.org/ ) offers *free, self-paced coding practice* across more than 60 programming languages‚Äîfrom Python and JavaScript to Rust and beyond. With a supportive community, personalized mentoring, and an *open source foundation* , it‚Äôs a great way to build real skills and get feedback on your code. Ready to take your knowledge further?

Start learning now! ( https://exercism.org/ )

********************************************************
Build a Strong First Impression with Your GitHub Profile
********************************************************

( https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/150827 )

Your GitHub profile can do more than store code‚Äîit can show the world what you‚Äôre capable of. If you‚Äôre aiming for internships, interviews, or new collaborations, having a clear, engaging profile matters. Check out this discussion ( https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/150827 ) to learn how to highlight your projects, organize your repositories, and make a great first impression‚Äîno flashy r√©sum√© needed!

Join the discussion ( https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/150827 )

***********************************************************
You should know: GitHub for Nonprofits has exclusive offers
***********************************************************

( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kHO1OvfOR7s&t=5s&ab_channel=GitHub )

GitHub for Nonprofits enables organizations to leverage technology to drive forward their missions and *accelerate human progress*. Verified nonprofits get access to a free GitHub Team plan or 25% off the GitHub Enterprise cloud plan. Do you work with any nonprofit organizations that could benefit from this exclusive offer?

Check out GitHub for Nonprofits ( https://github.com/solutions/industry/nonprofits )

*******************************
ORCA‚Äôs Catalytic Awards Program
*******************************

( https://www.orcaopen.org/ )

Looking for funding to support open scholarship and inclusivity? The *Catalytic Awards Program* from ORCA (backed by the Chan Zuckerberg Initiative) offers grants of up to *$15,000* to U.S.-based non-R1, minority-serving, or otherwise under-resourced institutions. Proposals can focus on community engagement, capacity-building, or networking‚Äîanything that advances equity and openness in research. The *deadline to apply is March 15, 2025*.

Learn more and apply ( https://orcaopen.org/work/cap )

******************************************************
Beyond the Classroom: Inspiring Careers in Open Source
******************************************************

https://dev.to/gh-campus-experts/beyond-the-classroom-inspiring-careers-in-open-source-56ld ( https://www.orcaopen.org/ )

Ever wonder where open source can take you after graduation? Discover success stories and real-world tips in this Dev.to feature ( https://dev.to/gh-campus-experts/beyond-the-classroom-inspiring-careers-in-open-source-56ld ) , showcasing *how student developers turn classroom lessons into meaningful community contributions*. It‚Äôs an inspiring read for anyone looking to grow their skills and broaden their career horizons in tech.
And remember, we are always keen to work closely with GitHub Campus Experts ( https://github.com/education/students/campus-expert ) !

Read inspiring stories! ( https://dev.to/gh-campus-experts/beyond-the-classroom-inspiring-careers-in-open-source-56ld )

There‚Äôs no shortage of ways to learn, grow, and make your mark‚Äîwhether that‚Äôs through an AI hackathon, a new certification, or an open-source project. We can‚Äôt wait to see how you use these resources to sharpen your skills and give back to the community. Until next time, keep coding and keep exploring!

snippet: Hi Anand, GTC, the conference for AI innovators, technologists, and creators, is returning to San Jose from March 17‚Äì21, 2025. You can join us in person or if you join virtually, it's free nvidia.
content:
Hi Anand,

 GTC, the conference for AI innovators, technologists, and creators, is returning to San Jose from March 17‚Äì21, 2025. You can join us in person or if you join virtually, it‚Äôs free nvidia.com/gtc/ <https://go.nvidianews.com/dc/M3tNI9WjhwgpWj9zFPExhmxG-PihWfL2KtRcdwRpuBupGF5r-ehK0fezyc9l57If36dUYM0LK75kdvXX0waslWILzQu1KswB-IWOITeHeL629CdoRJhtPP4TJwSCLPmbWkz4-8K2HyhCCuV8yIQhtS0pcEIxf2SSpJd-jq0r7iK-PxzyKK2xOWT7aYUxe0L13pk136QwkfA9hcxkYXqv9w==/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGYnSeNjjLjvXVgaIxEm6HpUWixmMfM6WzmU1Z0exDLnvxEph2ZLWYpCVFEpUIurmptZaldtsc=>. Either way, you‚Äôll get access to hundreds of technical talks and panels. You‚Äôll also be able to join workshops and training where you can get hands-on and learn how to build your own RAG agent and LLM application, or learn the fundamentals of a technology you haven‚Äôt worked with before. You can see the details here, nvidia.com/gtc/training/ <https://go.nvidianews.com/dc/M3tNI9WjhwgpWj9zFPExhsnT_U4PxfOT-1aeCZu0NcO9GnNrSbc-jC0dSAHd68pxNAJXG1Bp-VsoCGMoAgsDcwBEKz5IAYnEGP664hZamsyV2KLNkMXbZQaoge0FaY_jLfqzwf1GHx8_kGB77RcZiscKLG0n1itmLXqslII-snVrqUX_EKnFAGop4X0v8ZDnok2qKT7akoKkWYO7LYOnWUBXy3GbbdzCoRqc6anwHF4=/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGYnSeNjjLjvXVgaIxEm6HpUWixmMfM6WzmU1Z0exDLnvxEph2ZLWYpCVFEpUIurmptZaldtsc=> 

 Here‚Äôs a playlist, nvidia.com/gtc/sessions/gtc-developer/ <https://go.nvidianews.com/dc/M3tNI9WjhwgpWj9zFPExhlajTSoXi8sZXmdGPLxYztg6Dq6B4tFjoDVQ0FYLgIXPnXVJdD-bRKOG3DoNnx3bJ8Uv6EXSJejLdAN9xpBCHBrTRfbl4CPYIE1yMmCLeFDqIhDORpKvBy_hVbi_KAmwj0Mc0KBc0OPrK6HxFHLSdJK3WEwYHMXqmNtqNd5W0qJE4c9YA6z6ywFgpn79YyzoT-VZkbyP-PAeFvPWRFxbvCg=/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGYnSeNjjLjvXVgaIxEm6HpUWixmMfM6WzmU1Z0exDLnvxEph2ZLWYpCVFEpUIurmptZaldtsc=> of sessions I think will be useful for you, and help you build your 
skillset. Or you can access the full catalog, nvidia.com/gtc/session-catalog/ <https://go.nvidianews.com/dc/M3tNI9WjhwgpWj9zFPExhlajTSoXi8sZXmdGPLxYztgLxfJhtqa_DaA2YxHltXW3h8rXXlihV0jHOCGeMhQtJkmkriyH512ithKJmQWW7CfXM_eN457CFWKPwN3Nm2dPF_SQQUwqawvr_TBdj9O57RWn0SB5XfcMek23dAJjtQsk1cihqhi5fKV-X7Xq6Uznfpr9_fokjiV4FtxhMcp1zlWf7vhFgsqfEZgtUgOrzHE=/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGYnSeNjjLjvXVgaIxEm6HpUWixmMfM6WzmU1Z0exDLnvxEph2ZLWYpCVFEpUIurmptZaldtsc=>

Jensen Huang will also be giving his keynote on March 18 at 6 p.m. CET. It‚Äôs going to be an important one, packed with the latest technology news, definitely worth adding to your calendar now. Details and calendar link here, nvidia.com/gtc/keynote/ <https://go.nvidianews.com/dc/M3tNI9WjhwgpWj9zFPExhuSMaDjDPSnV3DF7J2rIkW3ULCLJtLokBss3Fuy_9D0CGL8Xh5pOLD0n6q5WfuSOk7kPN-oTj4eHSx7n3DAWQ3VJmvdhZ_GExFfCCvHn19gyMQIL0-otgtpC1HmYdnaty8Q7StKCtvSC1M3efsH-mGBCUsw5md0Q-WbJhXyx9jJvnW7GclDeEeytvuwjVlHcmA==/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGYnSeNjjLjvXVgaIxEm6HpUWixmMfM6WzmU1Z0exDLnvxEph2ZLWYpCVFEpUIurmptZaldtsc=> 

 If you do plan to join us in-person, you can use 
my link nvidia.com/gtc/?ncid=GTC-NVMH11RK <https://go.nvidianews.com/MTU2LU9GTi03NDIAAAGYnSeNjtg6XWEuiZrq2EjpA4EfyuJ4t2n3cLMmRFsWEwwucs3iClaXusBvCF7uK6CXPebUzLI=> to get 25% off your ticket. Discount code NVMH11RK should be applied at checkout. 

 Make sure you share this information with anyone you think will be interested. 

 Let me know if you have any questions and I hope you can make it. 

 Thanks,

 Adam Grzywaczewski

content:
Your invitation to participate in our survey focused on the current state of education and the impact of AI in the classroom.

( https://github.com/education )

( https://gh.io/classroom-survey )

anand-chaniyara-college,
We invite you to participate in our 10-minute survey ( https://gh.io/classroom-survey ) on the¬†current state of education and the impact of AI in the classroom. *Your insights will help shape future GitHub Education programs and resources* , ensuring they meet the evolving needs of both educators and students.

*Why Your Input Matters*
Your feedback will directly contribute to the *GitHub Classroom Report 2024* , which aims to inform educators, students, policymakers, and the general audience about the latest trends in the student developer ecosystem. By sharing your experiences, you're helping to enhance the educational journey for developers worldwide.

Take the survey ( https://gh.io/classroom-survey )

*Your Privacy Matters*
Your responses are completely anonymous. All data will be aggregated and reviewed only at a summary level, with no identification of individual participants.

*Thank You*
Thank you for sharing your valuable insights and helping us improve GitHub Education for the entire community.

Best regards,
The GitHub Education Team

subject: Kickstart Your Year with Our Cybersecurity ‚ÄúFind Yourself in the Future‚Äù Series!
snippet: View online Cisco Networking Academy Logo Dear Networking Academy Community, As we embark on a new year filled with opportunities, it's the perfect time to enhance your cybersecurity skills and
content:
Dear Networking Academy Community, 

As we embark on a new year filled with opportunities, it's the perfect time to enhance your cybersecurity skills and prepare for the future. Our "Find Yourself in the Future" series offers valuable insights into the dynamic world of cybersecurity, and we invite you to explore our latest webinars.¬†

Whether you‚Äôre just starting your journey or looking to advance your expertise, these webinars are designed to equip you with the knowledge and tools you need to elevate your career. Don‚Äôt miss out‚Äîexplore our latest events today!
Infrastructure Security - The Backbone of the Digital World
Discover the crucial role of infrastructure security in protecting our digital environments. In this session, Mike Bullard, a leader in Infrastructure Security at Cisco, delves into the technology that secures everything from servers to data centers. Gain insights from an industry expert and learn what it takes to excel in this field.
Threat Monitoring ‚Äì The Art of Cyber Vigilance
Elevate your cybersecurity expertise by learning the latest threat monitoring strategies. Join Daniela Herrera, Senior Technical Course Developer at Splunk, for an engaging session complete with a live demo. Discover how vigilance can protect against cyber threats and secure your digital assets.
Incident Response of the Network ‚Äì Navigating the Cyber Crises
Explore the Incident Life Cycle and the spectrum of cybersecurity threats in this enlightening webinar. Rachael Alagna, Leader of Information Security at Cisco, shares her inspiring career journey and offers practical insights into incident response. Understand the impact of data breaches and discover recommended Cisco courses to advance your career in cybersecurity.
Don't miss this opportunity to equip yourself with cutting-edge knowledge and skills. Watch these webinars to stay ahead in the ever-evolving world of cybersecurity.

subject: Secure Our World: October Cybersecurity Awareness Month
snippet: Your quarterly student newsletter from Networking Academy View online Hello Anand, October is Cybersecurity Awareness Month! As future tech leaders, understanding the importance of securing digital
content:
Hello Anand,




October is Cybersecurity Awareness Month!¬†As future tech leaders, understanding the importance of securing digital spaces is crucial. This month, through our Find Yourself in the Future series, we'll explore cybersecurity practices, from protecting personal data to defending against cyber threats. Read on for resources to strengthen your cyber skills!¬†

subject: anand-chaniyara-college, there's a lot to unpack here...
snippet: Amazing AI feats, events, projects, certificates, free learning resources... you should check this out. View this email in your browser Student newsletter September 2024 Hey anand-chaniyara-college, we
content:
Amazing AI feats, events, projects, certificates, free learning resources... you should check this out.

View this email in your browser (https://mailchi.mp/github.com/student-newsletter-summercode-5749115?e=6e3da3aa25)
https://github.com/edu/?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID


** Student newsletter
September 2024
------------------------------------------------------------

Hey anand-chaniyara-college, we‚Äôre already a few days into October but wouldn‚Äôt miss the opportunity to spotlight some of September‚Äôs events you might have missed, and point you towards all the great stuff happening this month!

In this newsletter, you‚Äôll find:
* Copilot is now available on GitHub.com
* Classroom hits 2 million students
* Your first step into open source
* GitHub Universe 2024 is near
* Setting up and securing your profile

* Students decoded 2,000-year-old texts
* GitHub Foundations Certificate
* Cod√©dex Campus Tour
* Microsoft Student Innovator Series
* Project spotlight: LeRobot


** GitHub Copilot is now available on GitHub.com
------------------------------------------------------------

Great news for students using GitHub Copilot with the Student Developer Pack! You can now use Copilot directly in your browser on GitHub.com, alongside your repositories, pull requests, and more‚Äîno IDE needed.

GitHub Copilot integrates seamlessly, helping you explore codebases, draft pull request summaries, and even troubleshoot GitHub Actions.
Learn more (https://github.blog/news-insights/product-news/github-copilot-now-available-in-github-com-for-copilot-individual-and-copilot-business-plans/?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID)
https://github.blog/news-insights/product-news/github-copilot-now-available-in-github-com-for-copilot-individual-and-copilot-business-plans/?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID


** GitHub Classroom hits 2 million students
------------------------------------------------------------

GitHub Classroom (https://classroom.github.com/?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID) has officially hit 2 million students accepting assignments, helping them gain real-world coding experience. Educators worldwide are using Classroom to streamline assignments and guide students in developing practical coding skills.

Thank you to all the teachers and students who‚Äôve contributed to this milestone!
https://classroom.github.com/?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID


** Your first step into open source starts here
------------------------------------------------------------

If you‚Äôre new to GitHub, contributing to open source can feel intimidating‚Äîbut it doesn‚Äôt have to be! First Contributions (https://github.com/firstcontributions/first-contributions?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID) is a beginner-friendly project that walks you through making your very first pull request. It‚Äôs the perfect way to learn GitHub, gain real-world experience, and start collaborating with the open-source community.
Get started with your first contribution (https://github.com/firstcontributions/first-contributions?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID)
https://github.com/firstcontributions/first-contributions?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID


** GitHub Universe 2024 is almost here!
------------------------------------------------------------

GitHub Universe 2024 (https://githubuniverse.com/?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID) is happening later this month, and you won‚Äôt want to miss it! Whether you‚Äôre a developer, student, or educator, you can join virtually for free (https://githubuniverse.com/?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID#tickets) and catch all the sessions live. From exploring AI-powered coding tools like Copilot to diving into the latest innovations on GitHub, there‚Äôs something for everyone.

Mark your calendars for October 29-30 and explore the session catalog (https://reg.githubuniverse.com/flow/github/universe24/attendee-portal/page/sessioncatalog?tab.day=20241029&mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID) to see the talks most relevant to you.
Get your free virtual ticket (https://githubuniverse.com/?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID#tickets)
https://githubuniverse.com/?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID


** Beginner‚Äôs guide: Setting up and securing your profile
------------------------------------------------------------

Ready for the next chapter in our beginner‚Äôs guide? This time, we‚Äôre showing you how to set up and secure your GitHub profile so you can start collaborating with confidence. Whether you‚Äôre new to GitHub or just need a refresher, this guide has you covered.
Check out the full series (https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL0lo9MOBetEFcp4SCWinBdpml9B2U25-f&mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID)
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T_PKBNImooA&list=PL0lo9MOBetEFcp4SCWinBdpml9B2U25-f&index=8&ab_channel=GitHub&mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID


** How students used GitHub Copilot to decode 2,000-year-old texts
------------------------------------------------------------

A team of students, equipped with GitHub Copilot from the GitHub Student Developer Pack, tackled an incredible challenge‚Äîdecoding ancient scrolls using AI. These crafty students applied machine learning to unlock mysteries hidden for centuries. It‚Äôs a powerful example of how GitHub tools are empowering the next generation of developers to solve real-world problems.

Want to learn how they did it?
Read the full story (https://github.blog/ai-and-ml/machine-learning/how-students-teamed-up-to-decode-2000-year-old-texts-using-ai/?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID)
https://github.blog/ai-and-ml/machine-learning/how-students-teamed-up-to-decode-2000-year-old-texts-using-ai/?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID


** Get ready for your GitHub Foundations Certificate
------------------------------------------------------------

Prepare for the GitHub Foundations certification (https://resources.github.com/learn/certifications/?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID) with a series of free Microsoft Reactor episodes available in Portuguese, Spanish, and English. Each session covers GitHub fundamentals, GitHub Actions, and security basics, helping you get exam-ready.

Even better, the GitHub Foundations exam will be available for free again soon as part of the GitHub Student Developer Pack (https://education.github.com/experiences/foundations_certificate?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID) . But if you‚Äôre eager to certify now, there‚Äôs also a big discount available.
* Portuguese series (Oct 2, 9, 16 at 11 AM BRT):
Register here (https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/reactor/series/S-1375/?wt.mc_id=seriespg_S-1375_webpage_reactor&mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID)
* Spanish series (Oct 5, 12, 19 at 6 PM CEST):
Register here (https://developer.microsoft.com/es-es/reactor/series/S-1388/?wt.mc_id=blog_S-1388_webpage_reactor&mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID)
* English series (Oct 10, 24 at 9 AM PT):
Register here (https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-developer-community/get-certified-with-learn-live-github-universe-series/ba-p/4244659?wt.mc_id=seriespg_S-1387_webpage_reactor&mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID)

Start preparing now, and stay tuned for the free certification offer coming back soon to the Student Developer Pack!
https://resources.github.com/learn/certifications/?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID


** Cod√©dex Campus Tour is wrapping up
------------------------------------------------------------

The Cod√©dex (https://www.codedex.io/github-students?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID) Campus Tour is reaching its final stop, and what a journey it‚Äôs been! Students across campuses have explored coding challenges and discovered the benefits of the GitHub Student Developer Pack‚Äînow with Cod√©dex included, offering tools and resources to grow their skills.

Missed the tour? You can still dive into Cod√©dex and the Student Developer Pack at your own pace. Learn more here (https://www.codedex.io/github-students?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID) !
https://www.codedex.io/github-students?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID


** The Imagine Cup is back! Join the Microsoft Student Innovator Series
------------------------------------------------------------

The 2025 Imagine Cup (https://imaginecup.microsoft.com/en-us?wt.mc_id=ic25_multichannel_student&mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID) season just kicked off, and you can start preparing with the Student Innovator Series (https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/reactor/series/S-1386?wt.mc_id=Social_S-1386_social_Student_Reactor&mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID) . Check out upcoming events to help you build AI solutions on the Microsoft Cloud and get competition-ready:
* Azure AI Sessions (Oct 12, 19, 26 at 10 AM PT)
* Founders Hub Welcome Day (Nov 2 at 12 PM PT)

These sessions are available in multiple languages, including English, Spanish, Portuguese, and Mandarin.
Explore the full schedule (https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/reactor/series/S-1386?wt.mc_id=Social_S-1386_social_Student_Reactor&mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID)
https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/reactor/series/S-1386?wt.mc_id=Social_S-1386_social_Student_Reactor&mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID


** Project spotlight: LeRobot by Hugging Face
------------------------------------------------------------

Ever wondered how AI can help with GitHub issues? Check out LeRobot (https://github.com/huggingface/lerobot?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID) , an open-source bot developed by Hugging Face that uses AI to automatically manage GitHub issues. It‚Äôs a perfect tool for developers looking to streamline their workflows and stay on top of project management.

Dive into the code and see how LeRobot works (https://github.com/huggingface/lerobot?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID) .
https://github.com/huggingface/lerobot?mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID

Thanks for being a part of our community! We‚Äôre excited to support your learning journey‚Äîstay curious, keep coding, and see you next month!

https://www.instagram.com/githubeducation/?hl=en&mc_cid=310ef8ff67&mc_eid=UNIQID

MATLAB

subject: MATLAB Campus-Wide License, Charotar University of Science and Technology
snippet: Greetings, Hope you are safe and doing well. My name is Harish Murthy and I am from the Education Customer Success team at MathWorks. I would like to inform you that Charotar University of Science and
content:
Greetings,

Hope you are safe and doing well.¬†
¬†
My name is Harish Murthy and I am from the Education Customer Success team at MathWorks. I would like to inform you that¬†Charotar University of Science and Technology (CHARUSAT)¬†has a MATLAB Campus-wide license, which is available for Faculties and the Students in the Institute.

Since the license is renewed all the students, staff and faculty members who are using the standalone/Individual license will now have to update the license file on their systems.¬†

Below are the steps to reactivate/update the License on the personal Computers:

1.¬†¬†¬†¬† Make sure the computer is connected to the internet

2.¬†¬†¬†¬† Launch MATLAB

3.¬†¬†¬†¬† If a license expiration error appears, close MATLAB and then attempt to launch it again

4.¬†¬†¬†¬† If prompted to sign in with your MathWorks account or SSO credentials, please do so

All faculty members, students, and researchers¬†have access to download MATLAB and associated products for use on personal machines using the¬†Charotar University of Science and Technology (CHARUSAT) MATLAB Portal.¬†Cloud-based tools are also available to all faculty members, researchers, and students, including:¬†
*MATLAB Online <http://app.go.mathworks.com/e/er?s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s=646005169&lid=13831&elqTrackId=dc66056e9c284bd6b99168d44222ec8c&elq=7c9fe4f3c3254c1895f6b91894aa0aeb&elqaid=5213&elqat=1>¬†‚Äì Run MATLAB in a web browser
*MATLAB Drive <http://app.go.mathworks.com/e/er?s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s=646005169&lid=12517&elqTrackId=197fc364cb274524afba44cde428cd2d&elq=7c9fe4f3c3254c1895f6b91894aa0aeb&elqaid=5213&elqat=1>¬†¬†‚Äì Work with your MATLAB files from anywhere
*MATLAB Mobile <http://app.go.mathworks.com/e/er?s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s=646005169&lid=16144&elqTrackId=e0bf56d23637408fae4483d516f2e5c2&elq=7c9fe4f3c3254c1895f6b91894aa0aeb&elqaid=5213&elqat=1>¬†¬†‚Äì Use MATLAB on an iPad or phone
*MATLAB Grader <http://app.go.mathworks.com/e/er?s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s=646005169&lid=18055&elqTrackId=11a8c9050fc043da83d94f714ccdcedc&elq=7c9fe4f3c3254c1895f6b91894aa0aeb&elqaid=5213&elqat=1>¬†‚Äì Create auto-graded course assignments with instant student feedback Online
*Online Training <http://app.go.mathworks.com/e/er?s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s=646005169&lid=3034&elqTrackId=d9c2da7956c442c384ec0ca61527418f&elq=7c9fe4f3c3254c1895f6b91894aa0aeb&elqaid=5213&elqat=1>¬†‚Äì Learn from online self-paced interactive training's

Charotar University of Science and Technology (CHARUSAT) MATLAB Portal Link: https://www.mathworks.com/academia/tah-portal/charotar-university-of-science-and-technology-31563870.html <https://app.go.mathworks.com/e/er?s_v1=5213&elqem=Blank-Email_Text_Sales&s=646005169&lid=38240&elqTrackId=7088ae8248b840d4aa16b7dec49e3245&elq=7c9fe4f3c3254c1895f6b91894aa0aeb&elqaid=5213&elqat=1>

For¬†installation issues, any student, staff or faculty member can contact our Install Support team ¬†at +91-80-663-26000, email:¬†¬†¬†¬†info@mathworks.in <mailto:info@mathworks.in>

Please let me know if you experience any concerns or challenges and I will be happy to help.

Thanks & Regards,

Harish Murthy
Education Customer Success Specialist
